{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":5,"timestamp":1772117672,"nonce":"ybTnhaGrCm0Zc0dEZ+UN3GDKWdk=","metadata":{"github-id":"LE_lADOQ241x87uLoC6zwAAAAVhP28A"},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772125854,"nonce":"ADFapO8PZj3987dB/F0ffe1Q28M=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sgpPJ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/274#issuecomment-3967980489"},"message":"## Triage Report\n\n### Scope Assessment\n\n**Well-scoped?** Yes — one script in, one script out. Clear inputs (filesystem) and outputs (machine-readable inventory).\n\n### Principle Alignment\n\n| Principle | Status | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Only what's needed | **Watch** | Currently zero project repos have governance docs. Script will find only workspace-level docs initially. Premature, or prerequisite that makes governance adoption visible? |\n| A change includes its consequences | **Action needed** | Removing `generate_knowledge.sh` requires updating `.agent/scripts/README.md` (references it) and checking `issue-252-script-intents.md` |\n| Enforcement over documentation | OK | Executable tooling, not just docs |\n| Workspace vs. project separation | OK | Script in workspace, scans project repos — correct boundary |\n\n### ADR Relevance\n\n- **ADR-0003** (project-agnostic): Must not assume `unh_marine_autonomy` structure — scan generically\n- **ADR-0005** (layered enforcement): Discovery tool, not enforcement — appropriate level\n\n### Dependency on #284\n\nScript needs to know where to look. If #284 unifies under `.agents/`, search paths change. Low risk since the script searches broadly by filename and can handle both patterns.\n\n### Design Questions\n\n1. **Output format**: Issue says \"machine-readable, one file per line with metadata.\" What format? Options:\n   - TSV (tab-separated values): `path\u003ctab\u003etype\u003ctab\u003esize\u003ctab\u003erepo` — simple, parseable\n   - JSON lines: more structured, easier for skills to consume\n   - Custom key=value pairs per line\n   \n   TSV is probably simplest and most framework-agnostic.\n\n2. **`layers/` is gitignored**: Script needs to use `find` or `ls`, not git-aware tools. Known workspace quirk (documented in `documentation_verification.md`).\n\n3. **Worktree awareness**: Should skip `layers/worktrees/` to avoid duplicate results from worktree copies of repos.\n\n### Concerns\n\n1. **No governance docs to discover yet**: Only workspace-level docs exist today. Fine as infrastructure, but can't be meaningfully tested against project repos until they adopt governance docs.\n\n2. **Cleanup consequence**: `generate_knowledge.sh` is referenced in `.agent/scripts/README.md`. Must update that reference.\n\n### Recommendations\n\n- Use TSV output (simplest, most portable)\n- Skip `layers/worktrees/` to avoid duplicates\n- Add a note about the `layers/` gitignore gotcha\n- Update `.agent/scripts/README.md` when removing `generate_knowledge.sh`\n\n---\n**Authored-By**: `Claude Code Agent`\n**Model**: `Claude Opus 4.6`","files":null},{"type":3,"timestamp":1772125930,"nonce":"ihROa5a731mHWUVAbgNVywpxVls=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDOQ241x87sgrDe","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/274#issuecomment-3967987934"},"message":"Let's wait and have unh_marine_autonomy have some governance docs to test.","files":null},{"type":4,"timestamp":1772137332,"nonce":"4kmwYTwnYG2HRGR0Bkvubyw5hkA=","metadata":{"github-id":"CE_lADOQ241x87uLoC6zwAAAAVh0uOF"},"status":2}]}